==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mahimahi
<hw>mahimahi</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>either of two large
slender food and game fish (<spn>Coryphaena equisetis</spn> or
<spn>Coryphaena hippurus</spn>) of warm waters. They are highly esteemed
as food fish, especially in Hawaii. See also
<er>dolphin{2}</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dolphin, dolphinfish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>lean-fleshed fish of warm waters, esp.
Hawaii.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dolphinfish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mah-Jongg</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>mahjong</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>
